{[%evp 0,48,25,17,19,13,39,19,20,-7,0,0,10,10,10,10,10,-2,2,-2,-9,12,-2,-4,8,
-5,-5,-4,39,28,31,-31,5,8,34,34,10,4,20,11,28,-8,-16,-12,22,5,27,-8,6,6,6]} 1.
e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. Ng5 d5 5. exd5 Na5 6. Bb5+ c6 7. dxc6 bxc6 8.
Bd3 Nd5 9. Nf3 {The most common and natural move. White keeps the flexibility
of his pawn chain and attacks the Pe5.} Bd6 {Undoubtedly, the best
continuation.} ({The tempting} 9... Nf4 {was played by many strong players,
including Nakamura and Karjakina. However, it is inferior in view of} 10. Bf1
$1 e4 ({Or} 10... Bd6 11. d4 e4 12. Ne5 $14) 11. d3 exf3 12. Bxf4 {Black
doesn't seem to have enough for a pawn. For instance,}) 10. O-O Nf4 {A
positional approach. Black liquidates the strong Bd3 and damages White's pawn
structure. True, it costs him losing another pawn.} ({Equally common is} 10...
O-O 11. Re1 f5 12. Nxe5 Qf6 13. Nf3 g5 {with wild complications.}) 11. Re1 {
White naturally focuses on the vulnerable Pe5.} (11. Nc3 {transposes to 10.Nc3}
) ({The timid} 11. Be2 $6 {runs into} Nxg2 $1 12. Kxg2 e4 {with a powerful
attack. Leicher, A - Zhou, L Willingen 2021}) ({The original} 11. b4 Bxb4 12.
Nxe5 {, as in Sangma, R - Sriram, J Noida 2016} {can be well met with} Qg5 $1
$146 13. g3 O-O 14. Bb2 Bh3 {, and White's king is in big danger.}) 11... Nxd3
12. cxd3 O-O 13. Nxe5 {The most consistent. On the downside, White's pieces on
the q-side remain undeveloped.} (13. Nc3 {is covered via 9.Nc3.}) ({In case of
} 13. b3 f6 14. Nc3 c5 {Black manages to fully consolidate the situation in
the centre.} 15. Ba3 (15. Ne4 Be7 16. Ba3 Nb7 {leads to the same.}) 15... Nb7
16. Ne4 Be7 {It is essential to avoid the exchange of bishop and unblock the
d-file.} 17. b4 {The beginning of interesting tactical complications.} ({
Also after} 17. Qc2 Qa5 18. Bb2 Be6 {Black has nothing to worry about.}) 17...
Qxd3 $1 ({Worse is} 17... cxb4 18. Qb3+ Kh8 19. Bxb4 $14) 18. Re3 Qd5 19. bxc5
Nxc5 20. d4 {White's pieces are somewhat more active, so we should see further.
} Nxe4 21. Bxe7 Re8 22. dxe5 Qxd1+ 23. Rxd1 Rxe7 24. Rxe4 ({Or} 24. Rd8+ Kf7
25. Rxe4 Bb7 $11) 24... Bb7 25. Re3 Bxf3 26. gxf3 fxe5 {The major
simplifications led to an equal endgame in Wharrier, J - Hoeppenstein, M ICCF
email 2015}) ({Harmless is also} 13. b4 Bxb4 14. Bb2 Qxd3 15. Nxe5 {We have
been following Sveshnikov, E - Balashov, Y Bled 2018} {The simple} Qd8 $146 16.
Nc3 Rb8 {would have offered Black a comfortable play.}) 13... c5 {Fixing the
weak Pd3 and unblocking the long diagonal for the light-squared bishop.} 14.
Nc3 ({White may try to solve the development issues by sacrificing the pawn
with} 14. d4 cxd4 15. d3 {, but after} Bxe5 16. Rxe5 Nc6 {he has to waste
another tempo for retreating the rook} 17. Rg5 ({After} 17. Re2 Bg4 18. f3 Bf5
{The superior development and weak Pd3 provide Black full compensation for a
pawn. Lukas,N - Claridge,J GER email 2017}) 17... Re8 18. Na3 h6 19. Rg3 Ne7 $1
$44 {Black has the better piece coordination. Pivinsky,E -Le Page,C ICCF email
2016}) ({Too aritificial is} 14. Na3 Bb7 15. Nac4 Nxc4 16. dxc4 {, as was
played in Stenersen, G - Storme, I Drammen 2019} {Here Black should have played}
Qf6 $1 $146 17. d4 cxd4 18. Qxd4 Rfd8 {The lack of development puts White in
a difficult situation.}) 14... Bb7 15. b3 ({Worse is} 15. Nc4 Nc6 16. Ne4 Be7 17.
b3 Nb4 $36 {Black took over the initiative in Savchenko, B - Howell, D Chess.com
INT 2021}) 15... Re8 {Forcing White to retreat the knight and unblock the
b8-h2 diagonal.} 16. Nc4 Rxe1+ 17. Qxe1 {White is still up 2 pawns, but Black
has an excellent attacking potential due to his powerful bishops.} Nxc4 18.
bxc4 (18. dxc4 {allows} Bxh2+ 19. Kxh2 Qh4+ 20. Kg1 Bxg2 21. Kxg2 Qg4+ {
with a perpetual.}) 18... Qh4 19. g3 ({After} 19. h3 Qg5 20. Nd5 Bxd5 21. cxd5
Rb8 $1 {White has to struggle for equality because Black will soon start
collecting the weak pawns.}) 19... Qg4 20. Nd5 {White has to block the
dangerous diagonal.} Bxd5 21. cxd5 Qd4 {Black quickly regains the pawns.} 22.
Ba3 Qxd3 23. Bb2 Bf8 24. Bc3 Qxd5 $11 {Black doesn't have any problems.
Elyoseph,H - Zejewski,P ICCF email 2018} *

